Following the latest update of Confluence OnDemand and the new global navigation, a page's breadcrumb trail now appears in the page not the toolbar.

The bottom pixel is being cut off for letters y, g, p etc - see attached.

When the Confluence language is set to German or French, the "Edit Macro" dialog shows HTML entities in the title.

*Steps to reproduce:*

# Set Confluence language to German or French
# Edit a page that uses macros, for example the panel macro.
# Double click the macro placeholder to edit the macro properties.

*Result:* Panel title is *&#8216\;Panel&#8217 ; Makro bearbeiten"* (see attached screenshot)

*Expected result:* 'Panel' Makro bearbeiten

h5. Workaround:
Append the following custom HTML after <head>:
{noformat}
<script type="text/javascript">
$.ajaxSettings.complete = function(xhr, status){
$('#macro-browser-dialog .dialog-components h2.dialog-title').each(function(i,h){ $(h).html($(h).html().replace(/&amp;/g, '&'));});
}
</script>
{noformat}

