{panel:bgColor=#FFFFCE}This issue is being tracked [here|https://bitbucket.org/atlassian/opensearch-plugin/issue/8/search-more-than-one-parameter]{panel}

OpenSearch does not work as expected when specifying more than one search paramenter.

Example:
# Create a query to to search the string "lorem" in Colfluence. The URL of the search is:
{noformat}<CONFLUENCE_URL>/plugins/servlet/opensearch?query=lorem&format=rss_2.0{noformat}
The results, as seen in [^OpenSearch1.png], are correct.
# Lets filter the results only to pages by adding {{type:page}}. The URL in this case is:
{noformat}<CONFLUENCE_URL>/plugins/servlet/opensearch?query=lorem%26type=page&format=rss_2.0{noformat}
Even when most of the previous results where pages, in this case the search return no results, as seen in [^OpenSearch2.png].

This happen for any parameters added. It only works fine if you specify only one search condition. For example this URL provides the expected results:
{noformat}<CONFLUENCE_URL>/plugins/servlet/opensearch?query=type:page&format=rss_2.0{noformat}

